22/06/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Mayor Dora Bakoyanni announced Monday (21 June) the start of a volunteer programme for the upcoming Olympics. In all, 3,000 volunteers will be selected to provide assistance to tourists visiting Athens during the Summer Games in August, and 60 information booths and kiosks will be set up around the city. The training of the first 600 volunteers has already begun. The slogan of the programme is "Show Them the Athens You Love".(ANA - 21/06/04)
